HB613 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 To alter, rearrange, and extend the boundary lines and
4 corporate limits of the City of Demopolis in Marengo County.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
6 Section 1. The boundary lines and corporate limits of
7 the City of Demopolis in Marengo County are altered and
8 rearranged to include within the corporate limits of the
9 municipality, in addition to the lands now included, all of
10 the following territory:
11 A parcel located in the East Half of Section 29 in
12 Township 18 North, Range 4 East, Hale County, Alabama and
13 being more particularly described as follows;
14 As a STARTING POINT, begin at the Southwest corner of
15 the Southeast Quarter of Section 29, thence proceed North
16 2,673 feet to a point; thence turn and proceed Northeastwardly
17 371 feet to a point; thence proceed North 1,561 feet to the
18 South right-of-way of U.S. Highway 80; thence turn and proceed
19 Southeastwardly along the South right-of-way of U.S. Highway
20 80 to the East boundary of Hale County Tax Parcel No.
21 36-22-09-29-0-000-002.000 (McCants Tract); thence proceed
22 South along the East boundary of the McCants Tract to the West
23 right-of-way of the new West Alabama Highway Project; thence
24 proceed Southwestardly along the West right-of-way of said
25 West Alabama Highway Project to the South boundary of Section
26 29; thence turn and proceed West to the STARTING POINT. Said
27 parcel containing 116.00 acres, more or less, in the East Half
28 of Section 29, Township 18 North, Range 4 East, Hale County,
